metadata.name: Why? #84
metadata.description:
The direction taken by the artwork Why? was taken when contemplating a canvas filled with what could be viewed as huge stone steps. I added the small stick people - were they climbing up or down? Where were they going? Where did they come from?
I then became interested in how subtle changes of background colour and changes of balloon colour changed the story, or the feeling of the story - ranging from bright hope to despair and futility. 

All p5.js.
The artwork is rendered at window size, use keys '2' and '3' to render larger.

metadata.name: SoulFish #223
metadata.description:
Named after the artist Wu Che-Yu, the soul fish was born in the void and crystallized from human emotions.

Fluttering silently and slowly, their bodies almost disappeared in the light of the deep sea.
The fish swims freely, and this is the happiness of the fish.
If we are not a fish, how do we know the joy of a fish?
How do we know that we do not know the joy of fish?
We will only learn about it when we come to the riverside.

Inspired by Zhuāngzǐ: "The Debate on the Joy of Fish" c. 3rd century BC

Interactivities:
> Key S: Save
> Holding mouse in different directions: Swim 
> Click and let the fish touch the Bubbles
> Key B: Toggle border
> Key P: Pause

metadata.name: Wordflow #11
metadata.description:
Visualizing variations of a paragraph about writing, structured as a binary tree, authored collaboratively with custom AI, and (painstakingly) handwritten.

Vector animation made by manipulating raw SVG code in vanilla JS, with motion based on an algorithm I first explored in the following dweet: dwitter.net/d/5107

The compositions extend far past the boundaries of your screen, but you'll be able to see a complete view in any SVG viewer or editor:

Press `s` (on mobile: long swipe down) to save current view to SVG file.

Press `r` (on mobile: long swipe up) to toggle reading mode, which will show each handwritten line in order, with fixed size and position.

Double click (on mobile: double tap) to show or hide the color palette extraction menu.

For color palettes, each token makes (optional) use of your webcam as well as any images you may wish to insert. (Please note that no images or video will be saved or sent anywhere, as all processing occurs locally on your machine.)

I had originally planned to use my own color palette extraction algorithm, as I wrote one myself a while back, but then I discovered Lokesh Dhakar's wonderful open source "Color Thief" JS library (github.com/lokesh/color-thief), which does a better (and quicker) job, and so it became this project's sole dependency.

rossgoodwin.com

attributes.name: Complete text
attributes.value: Words flow from the meaning like metal shavings from the grinding wheel. I watch the words pile up. The meaning grinds and shivers, proffers, offers itself; though the meaning may accrete itself from the words, from the writing, the meaning has been here -- has waited.

metadata.name: Imperium #395
metadata.description:
Imperium is a study of shapes and colors, and how a very small set of shapes and colors, when given equally simple rules, can create a great variety of patterns that may bring meaning to the viewer.

Press the s key for a quick download at the current resolution, and press the space bar to display the export and information menu.

metadata.name: Coronado #98
metadata.description:
This series is about the beauty and charm of imperfection, chaos amidst order, and letting go. It's about knowing that however much control we think we may have, things can all fall apart or burst into something unexpectedly wonderful at any moment, even without our hands tightly on the reigns.

Please see fxtext article linked from main project page for more background on the project and rendering notes.

Some key commands in live mode:

G : Toggle grain
S : Save current resolution
1 : 4000x5000
2 : 6000x7500
3 : 8000x10000
4 : 10000x12500
5 : 12000x15000
6 : 14000x17500
(1-6 work best on Chrome)
(rendering takes longer as resolution increases)

metadata.description:
A 10k Generative Profile Pic collection
GEN XYZ Das Occult - by culla - @tamccullough

move over cryptopunks
there is a new group on the scene

100% code - not an image composition

A bunch of common palettes
A selection of rare palettes
And a smaller set of ultra rare palettes
However, rarity will be based on what combinations the code produces

The majority of tokens will not have a special trait
However your token might have one or even multiple special traits
But, be aware that only the last special trait added will be listed in the features

Even then, look closely, because not all aspects of the canvas are included in the features. Collectors should still look closely and choose what they like when buying on secondary.

Which team are you on? X or O?

follow culla on twitter for updates. Or maybe __acolyte__

If the non reserved tokens mint out quickly, Access List mints will have 24 hours to mint reserves assigned to those wallets

Thank you for supporting an emerging artist in the generative art space

2x for each Basqunk held

share your tokens on social media with #genxyznft
